        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 12:30PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 1230 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Routon, or near Paris, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Haigler Ridge, Manleyville, Big Sandy, Old Springville, Buchanan,
India, Big Sandy Unit Tennessee National Wildlife Refuge, Sunnyside,
Van Dyke, Springville, Spring Creek, Porter Court, Paris Landing
State Park, Pine Hill, Routon, Henry, and Paris.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM CDT for
west Tennessee.</instruction>
